16/09/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Monday (15 September), President Ahmet Necdet Sezer met with his Portuguese counterpart, Jorge Sampaio, and said Turkey values Lisbon's continuing support for its EU membership bid. 
For his part, Sampaio praised the democratic reforms Ankara has implemented to meet EU requirements. 
At a joint press conference, the two presidents pledged to increase bilateral co-operation in various areas.
Also Monday, US Secretary of State Colin Powell told reporters in Kuwait that his government was hopeful that Turkey would agree to send troops to help stabilise Iraq. 
Ankara is expected to make a decision by the end of the month.
In other news, German Interior Minister Otto Schily arrives in Turkey on Tuesday to discuss the deportation of Islamist leader Metin Kaplan from Germany. 
Germany has refused to deport Kaplan, fearing he would not receive a fair trial in his home country. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, AFP, New York Times, Reuters, AP - 15/09/03)
